  "prompt": "How much should I expect to pay for a 1-car caltrain wrap advertisement?",
  "response": "The cost of a 1-car Caltrain wrap advertisement can vary based on several factors, including the duration of the advertisement, the level of customization, and the vendor you choose to work with. As of my last update, prices for transit advertising in general can range from tens of thousands to over a hundred thousand dollars for more extensive campaigns in major urban areas. \n\nFor a specific quote, I recommend contacting Caltrain directly or reaching out to an advertising agency that specializes in transit ads. They can provide detailed pricing information tailored to your specific advertising needs and campaign duration. Keep in mind that these prices can fluctuate based on demand, economic conditions, and special events or promotions.",
